<TITLE> Khaleda greets people ahead of Ramadan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia on Friday greeted the Muslim community ahead of the Islamic month of Ramadan. "Ramadan came up among us with a great message of self-restraint and self-purification," she said in a message. "The main education of Ramadan is to stand above all sorts of greed, attain Allah's mercy and abstain from all sin and injustice," she said. She said it is the duty for every citizen to strive to maintain peace in society by casting aside all difference and conflicts
